         Actually he does have a point in that as long as you arent hitting max hp on your vexes your number of hp wont really matter for how much you can lich considering vex heals the same and lich works the same no matter how much hp you have.</P><P><BR>But I still think for AE's, mobs that nuke, getting hit in melee, getting trained, feign pulling, getting out of tight situations, lifeburning, charm killing, slow killing undead, crowd control, liching where there are no mobs to vex if you dont have beads, liching on raids when you have a druid free to DH ( my name for the druid ch :D ) you and no mobs to kill at that time, killing tap immune mobs, dueling, pvping, taking HT's from mobs so that other people in group dont have to ( since you can just vex ), working CR's with feign so you dont have to use a coffin, getting to hard to get to places like traks lair solo, healing with shadowbond and the like, soloing when you are 2boxing a character that can cast large heals so you dont have to cast the mana ineffecient vex, mobs that rampage, mobs that summon, hp > all.</P><P>Im sure there are many more situations where hp is much more useful than extra mana, considering its really hard to go from FM to OOM on archlich even with crappy gear on.</P><P><center><img src="http://ickhor.homestead.com/files/ickhor2002.gif" border=0><BR>Sage Ickhor Quackmaster<BR>Level 60 Gnome Necromancer<BR>Brell Serilis Server</center><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
