			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=5028')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=77459&amp;TOPIC_ID=9014&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=HP+%26gt%3B+All%3F+More+like+HP+%26gt%3B+Thinking&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         HP is a very important aspect of developing a Necro, but it's not always the most important aspect.  It does on the other hand dominate a large portion of a necros developing life.  Before Angrier blows a blood vessel let me explain.</P><P>When a necro or any INT caster is young HP is NOT the most important stat.  INT is it's obviously.  Your first goal when it comes to equipment is to break 200 INT.  The problem is with today's equipment selection this is easy to do for most races.  You can do it non twinked (I'm not sure on Iskars, so forgive me if I'm wrong) by early to mid 30's thanks to the bazaar and the selection of money camps available to you at this level and earlier.</P><P>The next phase usually sees Necro's trying to get as much HP as possible to increase that buffer of virtual mana you can convert without dropping lich or tapping.  This peiod in a necros life lasts a long time, simply because the selection of good HP/STA items that you can afford to buy, quest or loot are not overly easy to come by.  This makes HP seem VERY important, but technically it's not as important as it feels.</P><P>Any extra HP over say your highest life tap/leech plus 40%, to prevent low HP agro, is just a buffer.  It allows you to delay the life tapping to get your HP back and gives you options in situations where things go wrong or you get distracted from staring at your HP guage while liching.  Idealy, no more HP is required than that 40% plus life tap, but no one wants to play like that for long periods of time.</P><P>HP is a very nice stat to have lots of, but more for the buffer than the virtual mana it might offer.  If you don't make mistakes ever or never get distracted/tired then your a necro machine and won't need the extra HP.  For everyone else for the most part once you get beyond 1750 - 2000 HP unbuffed your really at the limits of what extra HP can do for you in a day to day basis.  It just takes a very long time to get there.</P><P>If you are lucky enough to get into an uber guild or have lots of time on your hands you can now seriously look at FT and REGEN.   </P><P>FT is in my opinion much more important than HP after you get to 2000 unbuffed HP.  It lets you avoid having to lich and therfore life tap to regain mana.  The added mana regen from these items allows you to work with less HP since you won't have to lich as much to hit FM.<BR>Also, since your not using lich as much you are actually gaining more mana since your not wasting liched mana on life tapping or HP to full.<BR>FT also has an added bonus of working while you stand.</P><P>So if you can get it, FT is better than HP.  Once you get a nice HP pool to give you some options when you are playing then you should look for FT,IF you can get access to it.  I don't see me getting that FT 10 robe any time soon personally, so I will continue to work on HP and HP Regen.</P><P>That leaves REGEN This is kind of a funny beast for us necros.  There is very little in the way of it available and we really are using it just to make liching more mana efficent.  The biggest reason we want regen is not to replenish our large HP pools between battles it's to slow down the bleeding of HP while we are liching.  Regen items kind of act like poor man's FT items for us.  The more regen you have the less mana your wasting Lifetapping to get HP back from liching.  I  don't have a good idea what the ratio would be but, Regen effect could be coverted to a FT value due to the effect it has on our Liching for mana.  I imaging that the ratio is pretty small. Like 1 point of HP regen is like FT 0.33 or something like that.</P><P>Anyways so the gist of what I'm thinking is that depending on how far you are along in your necros development HP IS or IS NOT the most important stat.</P><P>Trolls feel free to flame me, call me a newbie and idiot or what ever else you might need to satisfy your ego's.  Everyone else give it a read and tell me what you think.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115390" target="_blank">Dartoth Ickorkin</a><BR>Warlock of Fraternitas per Honorus<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

