         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>Who cares how long he can last before lifetapping if HE STILL HAS TO GET IT ALL BACK???<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>I care how long I can wait to tap. Example:</P><P>necro 1 has 1khp</P><P>necro 2 has 2khp</P><P>In lich, BoD will heal you up to full if you're ~500 hp under max. In order to make efficient use off your tap (dot taps being most efficient) necro 1 would be at half health, while necro 2 would be at 3/4 health. Now then, who has the greater chance of surviving a train or multiple adds? </P><P>Or, necro1 has 2khp, necro2 has 3khp.</P><P>necro1 has to cast vexing at ~1250 to counteract demi/arch and heal to full. Necro2 does at 2250. Who has the most survivability at this point as well? I don't run oom very often at all. It usually happens when shit hits the fan and I'm doing CC, compacting the cleric/tank/who the fuck ever, tapping me health back, and whatever else i can do at the time. </P><P>Exp grinding? I never go oom. NEVER. (caps for emphasis only)</P><P>Raiding? Nope, don't run out then either, except those rare occasions as stated above.</P><P>My rank on items?</P><P>1)200 int<BR>2)hp<BR>3)right click effects(3 and 4 technically combined)<BR>4)regen/FT<BR>5)sta/resists</P><P>Is FT nice? sure, but not something I'm going to kill myself over since I regain mana fine as is. Regen? I'd love to have regen, but as was mentioned, there aren't a whole lot of regen options. sta/resists? sta is marginal increase for hp, but it is an increase and once over 100 resist in all areas, you don't need anymore imo. (raid buffs will take care of the rest)</P><P>int over 200 gives diminishing returns. HP is a constant that I'll always have and will continue to increase my surviveability. I hit over 2800 fully buffed a couple nights ago..I was giddy as hell. <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>My goal is 2.5khp at 60 unbuffed. My dream goal is 3.5khp unbuffed.</P><P>And why AA grind at 54? /shrug to each their own I guess, but I'll wait till 60 first. Or at least 59. </P><P>A fast recap- more hp=increased surviveability if shit hits the fan. I take alot of risks. I find them enjoyable. I find myself taking many many hits. HP>* for me after 200int. If you get by just fine with lower HP due to YOUR playstyle, then good for you. Don't worry about why I think HP is more important then. You've already made up your mind that it's not important for you anyways. /shrug, why'd this topic even come up again?</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264137" target="_blank" target="_blank">Charbonez Soulmark</a><BR>Clan Doomit<BR>Duzzil Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
