        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=77487&amp;TOPIC_ID=9014&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=HP+%26gt%3B+All%3F+More+like+HP+%26gt%3B+Thinking&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Most FT gear has +hp on them. You said who cares if necro A has more Hp than necro B they both need to vex/bond all their hp back, but it's way more efficent to be able to vex at half for necro A than it is necro B. Anything less than half and you draw aggro. </P><P>Angrier please try to listen for one second here these are the reasons for going for HP<BR>#1. Raiding (countless reasons)<BR>#2. Tanking (more hp = survival)<BR>#3. Lifeburn (more hp = more damage)<BR>#4. Pulling (skilled necros make amazing pullers, I've pulled KT who was taged pulled when no other FD'ers were there. Wouldn't have survived without HP)<BR>#5. Traveling (enemy lands, getting jumped by mobs)<BR>#6. Liching (simple enough)<BR>#7. Charm breaks (hp = more chance to FD or recharm)<BR>#8. Soloing (no need to explain)<BR>#9. Pacting (more hp = more pact healing with less danger)<BR>#10. Fear resisted ( guess counts as tanking)</P><P>Want me to keep going?</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
