			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1547')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=77489&amp;TOPIC_ID=9014&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=HP+%26gt%3B+All%3F+More+like+HP+%26gt%3B+Thinking&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         After 4 pages of calling angrier and idiot, i don't think my chiming in is going to convince anyone any further.</P><P>However, The statement Regen = Mana, not HP = Mana, makes me laugh my ass off.  In case you haven't learned yet, Regen (hp regen) is effectively increasing your hitpoints.  Why? Well, Lich and HP's are connected, quite intimately.  Start lich when your oom and see. Watch the following example.</P><P>Necro A) Zheart 1500 HP<BR>Necro B) 2000 HP no regen</P><P>Necro A will be losing hitpoints at 48/tick (assuming lvl 60), Necro B will be losing it at 53.  Necro B will be at 0 HP's in 37.7 ticks, Necro A (the regen one) will be at 0 HP's in 31.25 ticks.  The point?<BR>Assuming you are using arch lich, a Regen item gives you EFFECTIVELY 156 HP's (Necro A has the same Full health to death time as a 1656 HP necro).  </P><P>Now the arguement i've yet to see regarding mana and hitpoints is simply the fact of this.  Compare the damage/mana ratio on Vexing (By far our most efficient lifetap) to some other dots.</P><P>Vexing 1098 dam/495 mana = 2.218<BR>Pyrocur 1998dam/400 mana = 4.995<BR>Pyre (if your lucky) 2160/450 = 4.8<BR>Splurt 1600dam/237 mana = 6.75</P><P>Disregarding DPS totally (since we are talking about efficiency rather than rate) It looks to me like Vexing is less than half as efficient as pyre/pyro and 1/3 as efficient as splurt.  Now, WHY do you want more Hitpoints?  For soloing AND raiding?  </P><P>Hitpoints allow you the ability to use the other more efficient spells more often.  Thus increasing your ability to solo more mobs w/o stopping to med.  Regen level does help over time, as losing 48/tick over 5 hours is a huge benefit to losing 53/tick.  However, regen without hitpoints means that you will not get the full use of your vexing.  Having to heal yourself at 50% (assuming you play it safe) and the 1100 heal only gives you 800 hitpoints is a ton of wasted mana.  Getting an 800 heal for 495 mana is a huge waste of efficiency.  Granted the spell does the same damage as previously mentioned, but only healing you 800 hitpoints means you will have to use it again in 15 ticks as you are in the same situation as before, where as it takes 20 ticks to lose the HP's if you use the heal to full.  I'd say 30 seconds is a pretty big difference wouldn't you?</P><P>All that said, i don't think ND3 is the BEST aa for necro's.  I do think it is completely awesome and i love the 300ish hitpoints i get from it.  However, if you are talking about efficiency and mana pool, Spell Casting mastery is by FAR better for us.  Decreasing the cost of a 400-495 dot through specialization is absolutely awesome.  Considering all out major spells (Root, Dark, Lifetaps, Pyro/Pyre, Splurt, undead slows, fears) are all on Alteration, SCM is the most effective use of AA points in my opinion.  Anyway, enough logic for now, wonder if anyone agree's!</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
